channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: A Cicada’s Guide to Periodical Romance
item.description: It may sound like a mosh pit out there. But to the participants, mating is a delicate, sonorous affair, fraught with potential missteps — and fungal zombies.

item.title: Israeli and Hamas Negotiators Are in Cairo Under Pressure for Cease-Fire
item.description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was expected to meet the director of the C.I.A. in Israel, as concern rises about a broader attack on Rafah.

item.title: Biden never forgot ‘Build Back Better.’ Top aide says he has ‘unfinished business’ to crack the childcare crisis and help the sandwich generation
item.description: “President Biden sees the world from kitchen tables in Scranton, and will finish the job to give families more breathing room at the end of the month," said a campaign spokesman.

item.title: USC Tries to Save Its Graduation After Campus Protests and Arrests
item.description: The university is known for going all out on the ceremonies, but this year, after protests and arrests, the gloss is gone. Families are not happy.

item.title: St. Petersburg’s first Black mayor will consider a $1.3 billion ballpark plan that seeks to make amends for demolishing historic Gas Plant neighborhood
item.description: The Historic Gas Plant Project name is a nod to the once-thriving Black community demolished for the Tampa Rays' current Tropicana Field and earlier for an interstate highway spur.

item.title: Russia Hits Ukrainian Power Plants, Further Straining Energy System
item.description: The assault, a day after Vladimir V. Putin was sworn in for a fifth term as Russian president, is part of a wider campaign to cut off power to Ukraine’s civilians.

item.title: Time's up for Rolex? Cartier and Omega watches are holding their value better on the resale market
item.description: Average prices for Cartier watches are lower than Rolex and Patek Philippe, with many models changing hands for less than $5,000.

item.title: A Paused Arms Shipment to Israel, and R.F.K. Jr.’s Health Record
Kim Ki-Nam, Chief Propagandist in North Korea for Decades, Dies
item.description: Mr. Kim, who served under all three generations of the country’s ruling family, was likened to Joseph Goebbels, Nazi Germany’s propaganda minister.

item.title: Biden highlights $3.3 billion Microsoft plant in same Wisconsin city where Trump’s $10 billion iPhone plant never materialized
item.description: “Equally important as our own historic investments is the complete lack of investment on the other side,” Michael Tyler, the Biden campaign’s communications director, told reporters.

item.title: An Overlooked War
item.description: In Myanmar, poets, doctors and lawyers have traded life in the cities for jungle warfare.

item.title: Israel Reopens a Gaza Crossing Critical for Humanitarian Aid
item.description: The crossing at Kerem Shalom had been closed since a Hamas rocket attack from Gaza on Sunday killed four soldiers in the area. The closings disrupted the flow of aid.

item.title: Mercedes back-pedals on 2030 electrification target as EVs sales slow
item.description: The goal is now to increase sales of its priciest cars.
